HEADWORD: 1-dodecanol
<hw>1-dodecanol</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An insoluble solid alcohol
(<chform>C12H25OH</chform>) with an unbranched paraffin chain, used to
make detergents, such as sodium lauryl sulfate.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lauryl alcohol</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

